scripts/ — tee-vfhe setup, build, and run scripts

All scripts use `set -euo pipefail` and are safe to run multiple times
(idempotent where possible). Run them from the repo root.

SETUP & BUILD
=============

setup_tdx_env.sh
    Verify and configure the TDX + OpenFHE build environment.
    - Installs cmake via yum if missing.
    - Verifies GCC >= 9 and cmake >= 3.16.3.
    - Configures /etc/sgx_default_qcnl.conf with a PCCS_URL (warns and
      continues if the file cannot be created).
    - Verifies TDX attestation is available (/dev/tdx-attest or
      libtdx_attest linkage).
    - Updates the dynamic linker cache for /usr/local/lib.

build_openfhe.sh
    Download, build, and install OpenFHE v1.5.1 to /usr/local.
    - Fetches the v1.5.1 release tarball and the cereal header-only
      submodule (the tarball does not include git submodules).
    - Configures with Release, shared libs, native optimizations;
      disables examples/tests/benchmarks/extras.
    - Builds with make -j$(nproc) (falls back to -j4 on OOM).
    - Installs and runs ldconfig.

build_project.sh
    Configure and build tee-vfhe (server, client, benchmark runner).
    - Runs cmake + make in tee-vfhe/build/.
    - Reconfigures only when CMakeCache.txt is missing or CMakeLists.txt
      changed; otherwise preserves the existing build.
    - Verifies tee_server, tee_client, and benchmark/benchmark_runner
      exist and are executable.

RUN
===

run_server.sh [--port PORT] [extra args...]
    Start the TDX+FHE server in the foreground (default port 8080, or
    $PORT env var). Extra args are passed through to tee_server.
    Press Ctrl+C to stop.

run_client.sh [--host HOST] [--port PORT] [--workload ID]
              [--expected-mr-td HEX] [extra args...]
    Run the client against a started server.
    Defaults: host 127.0.0.1, port 8080 (or $PORT), workload toy.
    If --expected-mr-td is not given, reads the default from
    scripts/expected_mrtd.txt (96 hex chars = 48-byte MR_TD placeholder).

FILES
=====

expected_mrtd.txt
    Default expected MR_TD value (96 hex zeros placeholder) used by
    run_client.sh when --expected-mr-td is not provided. Replace with
    the real measurement register value once the TEE is measured.
